John and Janet Brennan bought Barnholm Castle in Dumfries and Galloway for just £65,000 in 1997 . 
  The fortress is thought to have been used by Scottish minister John Knox as a hiding place . 
  The Brennans have spent eight years and hundreds of thousands of pounds renovating the castle . 
  The property is now on the market for £695,000 but the couple will lose a six-figure sum . 
 